1
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:32,020
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,960
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:37,350
What do you mean

4
00:01:37,479 --> 00:01:38,680
"That's how it is."

5
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,039
Here's the thing—

6
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,560
Master's getting a bit muddled, right?

7
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,710
I was worried he'd mess things up

8
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:48,430
in front of Zhang Yunqi and his wife
at a crucial moment,

9
00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:50,070
so I talked it through with him.

10
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,680
I said,

11
00:01:51,039 --> 00:01:51,970
"When you go in,

12
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,229
don't say anything yet—

13
00:01:53,229 --> 00:01:54,229
just listen to me.

14
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,610
Wait for my signal.

15
00:01:55,630 --> 00:01:57,710
And once you get it,

16
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:58,350
you say—

17
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,170
'That's how it is.'"

18
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,200
That's how it is.

19
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:03,920
Master, right.

20
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,310
That's how it is.

21
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,400
How could they just

22
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,800
pop up out of nowhere

23
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,000
and throw their weight around like this?

24
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,360
Why should we

25
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,760
give up the house to them?

26
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,040
Keep your voice down.

27
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,590
Let me tell you,

28
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,420
if you piss Uncle off,

29
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,500
we'll be the ones getting kicked out.

30
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:35,870
We've taken care of this house
for so many years.

31
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:38,240
Even if we didn't achieve much,
we've worked hard.

32
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,710
The little money we collected from rent

33
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:40,770
was spent long ago.

34
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:43,610
Where am I supposed to
find the money for them?

35
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:46,120
Hey, don't eat the drumstick!

36
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,680
A duck only has two legs.

37
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,079
How am I supposed to serve it like that?

38
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:51,880
If I don't eat the leg,
should I eat the duck's butt?

39
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:54,630
It's good that Uncle

40
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:56,680
came back safely.

41
00:02:56,950 --> 00:02:58,110
It's just that,

42
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,560
all the things we did before

43
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:03,150
with Sister-in-law were for nothing.

44
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,150
Didn't you tell me,

45
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:10,410
your father told you

46
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,910
Uncle treated you

47
00:03:11,910 --> 00:03:14,400
better than his own son?

48
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,360
Then you should serve your uncle

49
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,800
like an even closer son.

50
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,630
Maybe

51
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:24,690
there's still room
to negotiate about the rent.

52
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:40,420
Makes sense.

53
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:47,240
Those drumsticks

54
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,500
must be given to Uncle.

55
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:49,750
At the refugee camp,

56
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,590
did you only see Master?

57
00:03:51,910 --> 00:03:53,240
You didn't see Mrs. Liu?

58
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,470
The two of them

59
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,000
must have really gotten separated.

60
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,770
But don't worry.

61
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,030
There are so many refugee shelters.

62
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,380
We'll definitely find Mrs. Liu.

63
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,140
Right?

64
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:08,150
Wanfu,

65
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,800
thank you for bringing Master back.

66
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,400
-Thank you.
-Madam!

67
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,840
I can't accept this.

68
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,269
I really...

69
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:19,600
That day,

70
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:22,310
I even slapped you three times.

71
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,800
You were right.

72
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:25,360
I am a fool.

73
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,630
If you can't get over it,

74
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:28,760
go ahead, hit me back.

75
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:31,270
Hit you back?

76
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:32,810
Madam,

77
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,830
I'm nothing but a lowly bug.

78
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,600
And you,

79
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,159
You're like a noble lady.

80
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:38,600
If a noble lady swats a bug,

81
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,690
then so be it.

82
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,600
It's nothing, really.

83
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,870
So what you're saying

84
00:04:41,890 --> 00:04:44,020
is that you're still holding a grudge.

85
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:46,480
Hit me then.

86
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:48,650
Look at you.

87
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:49,830
How come this noble lady

88
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:51,560
can't even take a joke?

89
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:52,750
Fine.

90
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,150
I remember

91
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,170
the three slaps.

92
00:04:55,310 --> 00:04:57,240
I'll slap back when I have a chance.

93
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:58,330
Then you remember.

94
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,800
I'll remember.

95
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,750
The most important thing right now

96
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:08,810
is to nurse the Master back to health.

97
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,270
And in front of Zhang Yunqi and his wife,

98
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,310
you must act convincingly.

99
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:13,910
Don't give yourselves away.

100
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,900
As long as this house is kept safe,

101
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,240
you can continue to live here.

102
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,220
By the way,

103
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,950
you must hide

104
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,560
the box well.

105
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:26,070
Those two are definitely eyeing it.

106
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:28,560
Don't give them another chance
to play dirty.

107
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:31,040
But the Master and I...

108
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,680
I'm afraid

109
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,560
we might not be able to fend them off.

110
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,870
Wanfu.

111
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:40,920
Can you move back in?

112
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:43,560
Move back in?

113
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,800
I know it's a bit presumptuous to ask.

114
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:47,480
It's fine.

115
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,390
If you're not willing...

116
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,360
No, no.

117
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,310
A place here,

118
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:54,440
and a place at Lutai.

119
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:55,840
It's fine.

120
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:57,680
As long as I'm back,

121
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,070
let's see if those two bastards

122
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,390
still dare to act up.

123
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:01,720
Thank you.

124
00:06:04,450 --> 00:06:05,300
Master.

125
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:08,480
Are you asleep?

126
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,070
Let's go downstairs.

127
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:11,870
Go eat your duck

128
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:12,870
and chili oil.

129
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,510
Let them bring it up here.

130
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,610
I want Yueming to eat with me.

131
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:20,150
Yueming is still young,

132
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:22,870
how can he eat your duck and chili oil?

133
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,030
That's true.

134
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:25,610
Master.

135
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,070
But,

136
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:28,510
we can have your nephew

137
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:30,800
bring your duck and chili oil up here.

138
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,150
We'll eat on the second floor.

139
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:32,720
Okay.

140
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,510
Let's go.

141
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:34,960
Let's go.

142
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:35,490
Master,

143
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,240
slow down.

144
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,700
Nephew!

145
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:41,000
Bring your uncle's duck and chili oil

146
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,190
up to the second floor!

147
00:06:42,190 --> 00:06:43,560
We're eating on the second floor!

148
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,240
Hurry up!

149
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,120
That's right!

150
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,480
You have a name now, you little brat.

151
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:07,790
[Xuzhou]

152
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:06,510
Come on.

153
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:11,570
Even if you can't aim well,
you still need to practice hard!

154
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,050
These old rifles

155
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:14,800
are older than my father.

156
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:16,480
The barrels are worn out.

157
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,620
Bullets come out drifting sideways.

158
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,680
Out of five shots, three miss the target.

159
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,120
Not to mention these rookies,

160
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,390
even I can't hit the target.

161
00:07:23,390 --> 00:07:24,450
And another thing,

162
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:26,000
just so the Japanese can see from the air

163
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,630
that we look fully equipped,

164
00:07:27,770 --> 00:07:30,120
we're stuffing them with junk
to make up the numbers.

165
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,130
Tell me—how are we supposed to
fight a war like this?

166
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:32,980
Yes.

167
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,870
Our equipment

168
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:36,670
is even worse than Yan Xishan's.

169
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,950
If we don't have food, we can starve.

170
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,360
If we don't have clothes, we can freeze.

171
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,630
But without bullets,

172
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,020
we can't fight this war.

173
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,920
The higher-ups surely know
we can't hold out.

174
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:45,690
So,

175
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,950
we must take the initiative,

176
00:07:46,950 --> 00:07:48,000
lure the enemy in,

177
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,600
and then use our superior forces

178
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,680
to encircle and annihilate
a group of enemies.

179
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,430
In short, for now,

180
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:53,190
we just have to use
our numerical advantage

181
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,390
to fight the Japanese to the death.

182
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:56,750
I don't want you to advise me
on how to fight this war.

183
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:59,360
I want you to advise me
on how we can survive.

184
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:00,790
We must survive.

185
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:09,920
Let everyone rest on the spot.

186
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:11,690
Attention, everyone!

187
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,190
Rest on the spot!

188
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:21,870
Their today

189
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,360
is our tomorrow.

190
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,210
I remember at Baijiazhai,

191
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:27,720
when Regimental Commander Liu
bid me farewell,

192
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,780
he said something,

193
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,040
"Uniforms

194
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,320
are our coffins."

195
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:50,630
Brother.

196
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:51,840
Come here.

197
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:54,550
Squad Leader of Squad Three.

198
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:55,750
Here.

199
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,020
Distribute these.

200
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:07,670
There's a Qijia Building
30 li away from here.

201
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:09,360
That's the Army Headquarters of 141.

202
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,840
Lu Yun, Chief of Staff,

203
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:11,960
is also there.

204
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:16,670
Zhou,

205
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:17,510
grab a gun.

206
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:18,390
I'll teach you how to shoot.

207
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,120
Okay.

208
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,080
Uncle,

209
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:25,320
see if there's anything
missing in this room

210
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,090
just tell me,

211
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,380
and I'll get it for you.

212
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:30,030
This is all set up

213
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,390
according to
your living habits in Shanghai,

214
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,500
Look at this table,

215
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,980
you can use it for writing.

216
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,020
By the way,

217
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,540
Uncle,

218
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:44,840
this is the hard coir mattress
you love sleeping on.

219
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:47,410
It's comfortable and good for your back.

220
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,510
Oh, right.

221
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:51,440
When we were back home,

222
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,320
you always

223
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,580
had a plate of
Double-Filling Sticky Rice Ball by your bed.

224
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:59,250
Taste it and see
if it's still the same flavor.

225
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:04,840
Uncle,

226
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,180
let me tell you,

227
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,200
we...

228
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:11,550
Our upstairs tenant's lease

229
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:13,240
just happened to run out.

230
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,170
Sister-in-law,

231
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:15,790
how's the fish?

232
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:17,120
That's great.

233
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:18,910
Sister-in-law,

234
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:21,440
are you comfortable
staying in that upstairs room?

235
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,100
That was my room to begin with.

236
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,300
Yes.

237
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:32,670
So now it's just returning it
to its rightful owner—

238
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:34,100
back where it belongs.

239
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:35,940
Uncle,

240
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,550
you really don't know

241
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,260
how hard Yunqi works.

242
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,510
He's just

243
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:41,690
too kind—

244
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,870
can't bear to see fellow
countrymen suffer,

245
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:44,320
so

246
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,870
he took them in.

247
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,600
Since the war started,

248
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,670
business at the foreign firm
hasn't been doing well.

249
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:50,360
We've just been relying on a bit of rent

250
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:52,080
to help cover the household expenses.

251
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,870
It's true Sister-in-law's had to
put up with a lot these days.

252
00:11:54,870 --> 00:11:55,700
But now,

253
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,630
fortunately, you are back, Uncle.

254
00:11:57,630 --> 00:11:58,600
Sister-in-law can also return

255
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,240
to live in her own room.

256
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:02,120
The worst is over.

257
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:02,840
That's wonderful.

258
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,390
Yes, it really is great.

259
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,150
Things have finally stabilized.

260
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:08,710
Uncle, you are the pillar of our family,

261
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,720
our backbone.

262
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,240
Yunqi,

263
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:12,870
Yujiao,

264
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:13,910
Yueming,

265
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:14,970
Wanfu.

266
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:16,270
Yueming?

267
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:17,630
Who is Yueming?

268
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,240
The kid has a name now.

269
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,240
Master gave it to him personally.

270
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,440
His formal name is Zhang Yueming.

271
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:25,870
Look at this name,

272
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,450
it's grand, poetic, and easy to remember.

273
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,380
Brother Yunkui is so blessed.

274
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:30,870
That's why I say

275
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:32,670
you are the pillar of our family.

276
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:34,630
Yunkui's son,

277
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:35,390
formal name,

278
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,080
Zhang Yueming.

279
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:39,150
Zhang Yueming, I'll remember it.

280
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:42,120
Yujiao, Yueming, and Wanfu

281
00:12:42,150 --> 00:12:43,880
arrived home a step ahead of me.

282
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:46,030
I've heard

283
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,720
bits and pieces

284
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:49,530
about what they went through.

285
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:50,640
From now on,

286
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:52,270
any of my ideas

287
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:53,510
or arrangements

288
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,200
will be

289
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,000
announced on my behalf

290
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:58,300
by Wanfu,

291
00:12:58,550 --> 00:12:59,910
Yunkui's good brother.

292
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:02,550
Okay, Master.

293
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,680
You two.

294
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:06,390
The meaning of the Master is this:

295
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:09,230
when this house was originally purchased,

296
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,150
it was right around the time
our brigade commander

297
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:13,270
Yunkui had just gotten married.

298
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:16,480
In the blink of an eye,
several years have passed.

299
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:17,600
All these years,

300
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,490
it's been the two of you

301
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,060
taking care of this house.

302
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,630
So you've really worked hard.

303
00:13:24,050 --> 00:13:25,580
Thank you for your trouble.

304
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:27,960
Master also said,

305
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:31,870
this house was entrusted to you to manage,

306
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:33,910
not for you, the nephew,

307
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:35,390
to act as a sublessor.

308
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,510
Also,

309
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:40,080
as for the Young Mistress—
she's just come back

310
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,880
and already run into all these
upsetting matters.

311
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:44,150
Don't be nervous.

312
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:46,320
The Master said something:

313
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,510
"Let bygones be..."

314
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,750
Bygones.

315
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,000
Bygones.

316
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,510
Let bygones be bygones!

317
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,120
But

318
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,190
for the previous rent

319
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,330
and the things you sold,

320
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:02,720
you have to carefully

321
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,120
calculate the accounts.

322
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,050
From now on,

323
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,850
whether it's the future rent

324
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:08,260
or the past rent,

325
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:11,480
our Young Mistress
will manage it personally.

326
00:14:12,030 --> 00:14:13,640
Is that what you mean, Master?

327
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,520
Yes.

328
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:17,600
Before, this house

329
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,200
couldn't be rented for much.

330
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,260
It only went up after the war started.

331
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,530
How do you expect me

332
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,000
to figure out this messy account
in such a short time?

333
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,480
What are you

334
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,560
chattering about?

335
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:30,870
Don't you know the Zhang Family
has strict rules?

336
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,010
As a junior niece-in-law,

337
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,670
how dare you interrupt the elders?

338
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,940
What do you mean?

339
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:38,810
Your wife interrupting here,

340
00:14:39,030 --> 00:14:40,360
is it because she has an issue

341
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,290
with our Master's decision?

342
00:14:41,290 --> 00:14:42,170
Nephew.

343
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:44,480
Uncle.

344
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:45,890
That's it.

345
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:48,360
That's not it, Uncle.

346
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,370
What Shuyuan said is the truth.

347
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,120
The pre-war rent
really couldn't be collected.

348
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,120
You know my position in the foreign firm
isn't high,

349
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:55,960
and that little salary

350
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,840
is not enough to make ends meet at home.

351
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,270
You see, with such a large residence,

352
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:00,910
the costs for water, electricity, coal,

353
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:01,630
and constant repairs…

354
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:03,630
They were really big expenses.

355
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,790
Uncle,

356
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,520
our family's own accounts...

357
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,930
Yunqi, let me ask you,

358
00:15:12,780 --> 00:15:15,190
did you sell

359
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,200
my Yun Shouping hanging scroll?

360
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,650
I didn't.

361
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,630
I really didn't, Uncle.

362
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:23,480
How would I dare sell your collection?

363
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,790
That's an authentic piece

364
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:26,840
I worked so hard to acquire!

365
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,670
I know. You...

366
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,630
You see, with so many people

367
00:15:29,630 --> 00:15:31,450
coming and going in this house,

368
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,240
you never know—
someone might've had sticky fingers

369
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,070
and taken it.

370
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,600
That's not

371
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,440
what you said during the day.

372
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,080
What did I say?

373
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,480
You said you moved it

374
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,290
while cleaning.

375
00:15:39,290 --> 00:15:39,750
You bull...

376
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,190
Tell me, where did you move it?

377
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,030
-Wanfu!
-Where?

378
00:15:47,020 --> 00:15:47,930
Yunqi,

379
00:15:48,930 --> 00:15:50,050
I said,

380
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,200
"Let bygones be bygones."

381
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,760
You should understand what I mean.

382
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:56,760
Understood.

383
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:00,780
Yunqi.

384
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:04,740
We Zhang family members
must behave properly.

385
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:10,030
I hope you and Shuyuan
will look out for yourselves.

386
00:16:13,590 --> 00:16:14,590
I'm tired.

387
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,620
Eldest nephew's wife,

388
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:28,400
hurry and boil another
pot of water for Master.

389
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:29,850
Take off your paper hat;

390
00:16:29,850 --> 00:16:30,880
aren't you tired?

391
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:35,260
Villains in power.

392
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:49,330
[Xuzhou]

393
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,570
This is too much!

394
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:02,970
They promised us cotton clothes,

395
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:04,640
but it's been delayed month after month.

396
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,160
They give us less and less supplies.

397
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,760
We don't even have firewood!

398
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,670
Zhou.

399
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,430
Squad Leader.

400
00:17:16,430 --> 00:17:16,990
Liquor.

401
00:17:17,050 --> 00:17:17,680
Zhou.

402
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:18,859
Wang, go get it!

403
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:20,910
Here.

404
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,700
Lie down. Come on.

405
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:29,440
Hang in there, Zhou.

406
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:31,920
Is it enough?

407
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,100
Change to a hot stone.

408
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:36,790
Hurry up!

409
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,250
Change to a hot one. Hurry.

410
00:17:39,770 --> 00:17:41,050
Hold it tight, Zhou.

411
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:44,930
Firewood is here. Hurry.

412
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,100
What happened?

413
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:47,900
Brother, he's frostbitten.

414
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:48,960
Hurry, warm him up.

415
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:49,760
Firewood is here.

416
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:51,360
Platoon leader, ice is here.

417
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:52,980
Melt the ice quickly

418
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:54,870
and boil it into hot water. Hurry.

419
00:17:54,930 --> 00:17:55,530
Be gentle.

420
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:56,600
He's coming to.

421
00:17:56,910 --> 00:17:59,250
Find a warm stone
and press it against him!

422
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:00,940
Add more firewood. Hurry.

423
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:12,020
I got you a travel pass.

424
00:18:12,590 --> 00:18:13,450
Leave right now

425
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:15,000
and try to get back before dawn.

426
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,430
[This certifies that Private Kong Erbao
is heading to Peixian
to procure military supplies.]

427
00:18:16,450 --> 00:18:18,170
[All checkpoints along the way
are to verify this pass
and let him through.]

428
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:30,270
Here.

429
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,680
Why is it so hard just
to get a fire going?

430
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,110
Hurry.

431
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:41,980
Hurry. Add firewood!

432
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:43,790
Keep him warm!

433
00:18:47,980 --> 00:18:49,820
Cheng!

434
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:50,720
Cheng!

435
00:18:51,410 --> 00:18:52,190
Do we have more liquor?

436
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:52,550
Yes.

437
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:53,000
Hurry!

438
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,160
Go get the liquor!

439
00:18:56,320 --> 00:19:01,440
[Shanghai]

440
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:13,190
Uncle.

441
00:19:14,030 --> 00:19:14,790
Uncle.

442
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,710
Take a look.

443
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,600
Look at what this is.

444
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,220
Clear-Stewed Nanjing Chicken with Ham.

445
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:24,900
You have good eyes.

446
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:25,800
Come.

447
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:29,020
I haven't seen this in a long time.

448
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:44,550
Have a taste.

449
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:46,110
Have a taste.

450
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:47,070
Okay.

451
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:49,460
This is a five-month-old pullet.

452
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:58,750
Uncle,

453
00:19:59,550 --> 00:20:00,000
I got it

454
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,450
from the Jinling Restaurant for you.

455
00:20:02,590 --> 00:20:04,000
I even tracked down Chef Mu—

456
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,000
the same one who used to cook for you.

457
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,750
When you used to come to Shanghai,

458
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,160
didn't you like this?

459
00:20:09,470 --> 00:20:10,560
You always said,

460
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:14,930
the chicken was fresh and tender,
the meat soft and delicate,

461
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,510
the broth rich and clear, pale in color.

462
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:20,030
Does it still taste the same?

463
00:20:21,030 --> 00:20:21,930
Yunqi,

464
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,750
the situation is turbulent now.

465
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:27,640
Save whatever we can.

466
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:30,620
Don't waste like this again.

467
00:20:32,050 --> 00:20:32,900
Yes.

468
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:36,000
Life is indeed hard now.

469
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:37,570
But

470
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:38,960
just take it as my

471
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,550
filial piety to you.

472
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,070
To be honest,

473
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,240
I haven't had meat for half a month.

474
00:20:46,790 --> 00:20:48,480
I'm responding to the call

475
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:50,480
and eating patriotic vegetarian food.

476
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,590
The money saved

477
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:54,280
has all been donated as savings donations.

478
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,770
Don't you get a salary
at the foreign firm?

479
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:00,170
Please drink the soup while it's hot.

480
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:02,230
Whatever little I earn,

481
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:04,270
one day it goes to savings
for disaster relief,

482
00:21:04,270 --> 00:21:06,670
the next to national salvation donations,

483
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,160
and the day after

484
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:10,770
there are public fundraisers
on the street—

485
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:11,960
I give to all of them.

486
00:21:12,830 --> 00:21:14,970
Do you know how high prices

487
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,720
are in the concession now?

488
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:19,750
Meat and fish are incredibly expensive.

489
00:21:20,830 --> 00:21:22,180
I really don't know what to do.

490
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:23,330
Since you are here,

491
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:25,310
I can't let you go hungry.

492
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:26,880
Uncle,

493
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,270
all these years,

494
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:29,960
I've just wanted a child,

495
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,550
but I just couldn't get one.

496
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:33,910
When I go out

497
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:37,630
and see those things like sea horses,
sea dragons, and seal pizzle…

498
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:36,390
[Essence of rose]

499
00:21:37,650 --> 00:21:39,480
I don't even dare to look at
the whole ones.

500
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,810
I can only buy some scraps
to boil and drink.

501
00:21:41,810 --> 00:21:44,270
But what nutrition
could those scraps have?

502
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,550
When night comes,

503
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:50,000
I just stare wide-eyed until dawn.

504
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:53,790
My hair falls out in handfuls.

505
00:21:55,350 --> 00:21:56,350
Uncle,

506
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:58,430
look at my hair.

507
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,090
It's fake.

508
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,510
I'm almost completely bald.

509
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:03,240
Yunqi, don't cry.

510
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:03,640
Uncle.

511
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,030
Don't cry.

512
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:07,000
I don't need nutrition.

513
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:09,830
I know your difficulties.

514
00:22:12,890 --> 00:22:16,440
We are not the only ones
having a hard time,

515
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:18,540
and it won't just be for a day or two.

516
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:21,270
It's a long-term war of resistance.

517
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:23,510
Things might get even worse.

518
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:27,400
But Yunqi, don't lose heart.

519
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:29,110
We will endure it together,

520
00:22:29,110 --> 00:22:30,510
and we'll get through it.

521
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:37,080
As for the past rent

522
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:39,990
and all those miscellaneous accounts,

523
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:41,910
we'll just forget about them.

524
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:42,640
Uncle.

525
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:43,980
-From now on…
-Listen to me,

526
00:22:43,980 --> 00:22:46,220
I have known that you loved me the most
since I was little.

527
00:22:46,220 --> 00:22:47,200
Even my father said

528
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,720
you are more of a father to me than he is.

529
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:50,960
Rest assured.

530
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:53,030
You can stay here peacefully.

531
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,830
Even though Yunkui isn't by your side,

532
00:22:54,830 --> 00:22:55,760
you have Yunqi.

533
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:57,920
I will make sure you are comfortable

534
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,850
and healthy.

535
00:22:59,000 --> 00:22:59,950
Here's the thing.

536
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:01,360
From now on,

537
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,150
you and Shuyuan
won't need to collect the rent.

538
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:07,110
I'll leave this burden to Yujiao.

539
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,110
That won't do.

540
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,480
Uncle,

541
00:23:11,650 --> 00:23:13,010
Sister-in-law has just
arrived in Shanghai.

542
00:23:13,010 --> 00:23:14,070
She is unfamiliar with
the place and the people.

543
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:15,800
She can't do this.

544
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:16,980
Taku vegetables

545
00:23:17,010 --> 00:23:18,790
cost three cents on this street,

546
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:19,920
but two streets over

547
00:23:20,070 --> 00:23:22,000
it's nine cents—triple the price.

548
00:23:22,070 --> 00:23:23,450
A bar of soap

549
00:23:23,470 --> 00:23:25,000
that costs four cents here

550
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:27,270
is four dollars just a few streets away.

551
00:23:27,270 --> 00:23:29,030
Japanese goods are cheap.

552
00:23:29,030 --> 00:23:30,960
Uncle, we are Chinese.

553
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,980
We must have a sense of shame.

554
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,390
We can't buy Japanese goods, right?

555
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:36,850
[Laundry Soap]

556
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:36,840
Even on the same street,

557
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:38,480
figuring out whose vegetables are fresh

558
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:40,070
and whose are cheap—

559
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:42,440
it's really a whole science.

560
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:44,340
Shanghai

561
00:23:44,740 --> 00:23:47,330
may look glamorous on the outside,

562
00:23:47,450 --> 00:23:48,990
but underneath,

563
00:23:49,110 --> 00:23:52,230
everything—people, morals, and order—
is completely chaotic.

564
00:23:52,230 --> 00:23:52,990
Uncle,

565
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:56,220
things here are far more complicated
than they appear.

566
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:59,920
How complicated can things
in Shanghai really be?

567
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:01,920
Can it drown people?

568
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:03,830
In my opinion,

569
00:24:03,860 --> 00:24:05,130
it's all

570
00:24:05,270 --> 00:24:06,110
just

571
00:24:06,370 --> 00:24:08,110
superficial—nothing deep at all,

572
00:24:08,110 --> 00:24:09,200
right, Master?

573
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,600
That's how it is.

574
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:15,200
Master,

575
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:17,070
you look in great spirits today.

576
00:24:17,820 --> 00:24:18,450
Look.

577
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,270
My Four Treasures of the Study.

578
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:22,070
Yes, yes.

579
00:24:22,230 --> 00:24:23,360
I bought them

580
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,590
according to your list.

581
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:25,200
Good.

582
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:25,530
Come.

583
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,920
I forgot to report to the Young Master.

584
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:29,850
These things

585
00:24:30,030 --> 00:24:32,340
were bought on credit

586
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,310
from Jingxin Pavilion
at the alley entrance.

587
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:35,480
Why didn't you pay?

588
00:24:36,110 --> 00:24:37,400
They were all put on your account.

589
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,270
The boss said he has a great relationship
with you.

590
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,870
Master, come and take a look.

591
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:41,680
This brush

592
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:43,240
is the finest Huzhou brush.

593
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,500
Good.

594
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:45,700
And this inkstone,

595
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:47,180
the finest Duan inkstone.

596
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:48,830
Oh, by the way,

597
00:24:48,850 --> 00:24:49,590
the boss said

598
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:51,480
Xuan paper has been out of stock
these past couple of days.

599
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,480
Once it's available in a few days,

600
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,630
he'll send it over

601
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,480
and put it on the Young Master's tab.

602
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,680
Good.

603
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:57,790
Look at this too.

604
00:24:58,510 --> 00:24:59,680
Paperweight.

605
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,500
The boss said he felt bad,

606
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,480
so he gave it for free.

607
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,590
Why didn't you

608
00:25:03,590 --> 00:25:05,090
get a brush stand for Master?

609
00:25:05,090 --> 00:25:06,160
It makes you, a Meng,

610
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,960
look like such a loyal servant
of our Zhang family.

611
00:25:09,510 --> 00:25:11,070
The Young Master is right.

612
00:25:11,270 --> 00:25:12,720
That's a great reminder.

613
00:25:13,430 --> 00:25:16,070
I must get a complete set

614
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,510
for our Master.

615
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,240
I'll go right now.

616
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,720
Don't push your luck.

617
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,710
Stop messing around

618
00:25:24,830 --> 00:25:26,890
with all this petty, low-class junk.

619
00:25:27,530 --> 00:25:28,440
Uncle,

620
00:25:29,880 --> 00:25:31,720
if you don't drink this chicken soup,

621
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,720
it'll get cold.

622
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:39,000
In Shanghai, no matter
how complicated things get,

623
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,880
those who know how to navigate
the currents won't go under.

624
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,400
That's how it is.

625
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:44,760
Master,

626
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:46,710
let me show you another good thing.

627
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:50,670
A brush holder.

628
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,010
Isn't it beautiful?

629
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,050
How did it go?

630
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:03,070
He doesn't want the previous rent
and the money

631
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:04,730
from selling things anymore.

632
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:06,660
He's your Uncle after all.

633
00:26:06,660 --> 00:26:07,590
Bullshit.

634
00:26:08,310 --> 00:26:09,110
The future...

635
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,460
There's "future"?

636
00:26:11,350 --> 00:26:12,540
The future rent

637
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,970
still has to be managed by Sister-in-law.

638
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:15,960
See,

639
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:18,240
he's still her biological father.

640
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,570
What should we do?

641
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:24,000
Hei San is pressing for money again.

642
00:26:24,270 --> 00:26:26,590
Just now he blocked me
at the alley entrance

643
00:26:26,590 --> 00:26:28,720
and forced me to watch him kill a chicken.

644
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,350
He said this time he killed a chicken;

645
00:26:30,350 --> 00:26:31,810
next time it'll be me.

646
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:32,640
Just now,

647
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:35,000
you didn't see the look in
that chicken's eyes before it died.

648
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,600
Isn't it just like your look?

649
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:39,000
So I say,

650
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:41,640
you can't even pretend to be a real son,

651
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,880
and you can't even play the role
of a traitor properly.

652
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:45,310
The Japanese are so vicious,

653
00:26:45,310 --> 00:26:46,880
and they're still eyeing our house.

654
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,510
They really think they own the world.

655
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:49,830
And you're just being so submissive,

656
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:51,590
you can't even handle your own Uncle.

657
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:54,280
We don't have the rent money
for next month.

658
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:57,350
With your meager salary
from the foreign firm,

659
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:58,920
will we starve to death

660
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,650
or be killed by the loan sharks?

661
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:02,640
Figure it out yourself.

662
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:05,040
They scare me, and you scare me too?

663
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:07,310
Master, here's the water.

664
00:27:08,550 --> 00:27:10,000
Come, come, come.

665
00:27:10,110 --> 00:27:12,920
The chaos of war
really ruins the art of painting.

666
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:15,720
It's been so long
since I last picked up a brush

667
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:17,380
that my hand feels a bit rusty.

668
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,910
I can go without fish for my meals,

669
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,600
or a carriage for my travels,

670
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:26,100
but I cannot go a day
without my brush and ink.

671
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,810
You just sobered up a bit,

672
00:27:27,810 --> 00:27:29,880
and you're already quoting classics.

673
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:30,920
Hurry up and write,

674
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:33,250
so I can sell it for money
when you're done.

675
00:27:35,010 --> 00:27:37,820
You have no culture.
All you know is money.

676
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:39,070
I think

677
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:42,720
you just need a good beating
from a tutor.

678
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:44,920
Master,

679
00:27:45,110 --> 00:27:46,840
look at what you're wearing.

680
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:48,180
A silk jacket,

681
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:49,490
and a velvet vest—

682
00:27:49,510 --> 00:27:51,220
these are all high-end goods.

683
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:52,700
This was all bought with Xiaoyue's

684
00:27:52,700 --> 00:27:54,440
savings from years ago,

685
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:56,000
and my travel expenses to Wuhan,

686
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,630
to get you this outfit.

687
00:27:57,750 --> 00:27:58,970
Look at this too,

688
00:27:59,030 --> 00:27:59,750
do you see,

689
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:00,510
this beard brush?

690
00:28:00,510 --> 00:28:02,440
I bought this with my own money too.

691
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:03,780
Wanfu,

692
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:08,160
are you afraid I'll default on
the money for my clothes?

693
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:10,430
I'll pay you back double in a few days.

694
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:11,660
Come over and warm up.

695
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:13,830
By the way,

696
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,990
did that jerk Zhang Yunqi

697
00:28:17,010 --> 00:28:19,170
come crying to you about being poor?

698
00:28:20,650 --> 00:28:21,800
Did he tell you

699
00:28:21,830 --> 00:28:23,440
he bought government bonds
with all his money,

700
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,570
or donated it?

701
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:26,830
The rent for the house...

702
00:28:26,830 --> 00:28:27,630
Don't budge

703
00:28:27,660 --> 00:28:29,150
on the rent.

704
00:28:29,170 --> 00:28:30,030
If you do,

705
00:28:30,030 --> 00:28:31,860
we won't get a single penny.

706
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:41,090
He didn't already cry to you
about his misery, did he?

707
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:42,460
Wait,

708
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:44,270
you didn't already agree

709
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:45,730
to waive his rent, did you?

710
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:50,350
Master, there's my money in that rent!

711
00:28:51,510 --> 00:28:52,490
Wanfu.

712
00:28:52,510 --> 00:28:53,900
Wanfu, look.

713
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:58,030
Yunqi has had it hard enough.

714
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,560
He was just here,

715
00:29:00,030 --> 00:29:01,640
crying his eyes out.

716
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:05,310
You've got to know when to draw the line.

717
00:29:06,390 --> 00:29:07,460
If you push him any further,

718
00:29:07,460 --> 00:29:09,310
won't that be going too far?

719
00:29:09,340 --> 00:29:11,410
What are you talking about?

720
00:29:11,510 --> 00:29:12,490
Who's bullying whom?

721
00:29:12,490 --> 00:29:14,440
How did it suddenly
become me going too far?

722
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:15,240
-Isn't this just biting the hand
that feeds you—
-Let me have a look.

723
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,830
no appreciation for kindness?

724
00:29:16,830 --> 00:29:17,740
Who are you calling a dog?

725
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:18,450
Wanfu,

726
00:29:22,270 --> 00:29:23,930
are you spinning yarns again?

727
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,200
Master was bored,

728
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,410
so I was telling him "General Yue Fei".

729
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:30,990
That's not what happened.

730
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:33,220
Master,

731
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:35,000
the chicken soup your nephew brought

732
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,790
will get cold if you don't drink it.

733
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:37,880
It'll be a waste if it gets cold.

734
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,590
Are you going to drink it?

735
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:39,480
No.

736
00:29:39,710 --> 00:29:41,460
If you won't, I will.

737
00:29:41,490 --> 00:29:43,710
Wasting food is a sin.

738
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:52,210
[Wuhan]

739
00:29:48,550 --> 00:29:51,160
My mother and I fled
from Northern Jiangsu to Shanghai

740
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,560
when I was only fourteen.

741
00:29:52,850 --> 00:29:54,420
If we hadn't met Wanfu,

742
00:29:55,130 --> 00:29:57,990
my mother and I would
have starved to death long ago.

743
00:29:58,650 --> 00:30:00,000
He's stingy, yes—

744
00:30:00,070 --> 00:30:02,800
but when it came to helping us,
he never held back.

745
00:30:03,030 --> 00:30:04,240
He always said

746
00:30:04,590 --> 00:30:05,650
that when he saw me,

747
00:30:05,790 --> 00:30:07,070
it was like seeing his younger self

748
00:30:07,070 --> 00:30:10,000
when he first came to
Shanghai from Shandong to make a living.

749
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,730
Later, when my mother got sick,

750
00:30:12,270 --> 00:30:13,960
he took great care of her.

751
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:18,090
In the end, he helped me bury my mother.

752
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:21,010
We were both orphans with nowhere to turn,

753
00:30:21,030 --> 00:30:22,890
and could only rely on ourselves.

754
00:30:23,030 --> 00:30:25,090
Surviving was the greatest victory.

755
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:26,480
Yes.

756
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:28,920
Wanfu was a loyal and righteous man.

757
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:30,510
Miss,

758
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,510
I know you look down on him.

759
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,110
He just wanted to live.

760
00:30:34,110 --> 00:30:36,440
All he thought about was food and clothes.

761
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:38,070
His only wish

762
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:39,350
was for us to save money together

763
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:40,510
and open a bun shop.

764
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,030
Xiaoyue,

765
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:44,550
don't be so sad.

766
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:47,080
Over the past few months,

767
00:30:47,830 --> 00:30:50,000
we have experienced
so much life and death.

768
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,330
Even if we stay away from the battlefield,

769
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:53,730
there are so many people

770
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:54,610
who starved,

771
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:55,400
were bombed, or died in vain—

772
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,920
-too many to count.
-But Wanfu is different.

773
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:59,360
He died in battle.

774
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:01,160
Even if he was just a small soldier—

775
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,240
just a nobody—

776
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,160
he still died for his country.

777
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,760
He is an anti-Japanese hero.

778
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,740
Yes.

779
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,000
He is an anti-Japanese hero.

780
00:31:11,110 --> 00:31:12,350
He had no parents

781
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:13,960
or any brothers.

782
00:31:14,510 --> 00:31:17,400
There must be someone
in this world who remembers him.

783
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:18,510
He still has me.

784
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,420
I am the daughter-in-law
of the Meng family.

785
00:31:21,550 --> 00:31:23,210
I want to build a grave for him.

786
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:27,160
Xiaoyue!

787
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:32,850
Father,

788
00:31:34,030 --> 00:31:36,360
I plan to go out
and look for a job tomorrow.

789
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,950
I've talked to Auntie Jing.

790
00:31:39,950 --> 00:31:41,150
When I go out,

791
00:31:41,180 --> 00:31:43,240
she will help me take care of Yueming.

792
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:46,350
Yujiao,

793
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:50,640
we traveled all the way to Shanghai,

794
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:52,980
only to end up in such a state.

795
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:55,310
You've suffered.

796
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:55,910
Father,

797
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:56,970
whatever life brings,

798
00:31:56,970 --> 00:31:58,650
we'll just live accordingly.

799
00:31:58,960 --> 00:31:59,790
I can't let my studies

800
00:31:59,790 --> 00:32:01,440
go to waste.

801
00:32:01,630 --> 00:32:03,010
I actually like working.

802
00:32:03,010 --> 00:32:05,290
I think earning my own living
is a good thing.

803
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:07,290
There is no such thing as suffering.

804
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,710
All right.

805
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:12,700
Had enough to eat?

806
00:32:13,380 --> 00:32:15,780
Let me talk to you about
something serious.

807
00:32:16,090 --> 00:32:18,900
I've heard that in some places
the postal routes have reopened.

808
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:19,510
Do you have a way

809
00:32:19,510 --> 00:32:21,680
to find out Xiaoyue's address in Wuhan?

810
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:22,920
You can write letters now.

811
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,000
Really?

812
00:32:24,990 --> 00:32:25,830
But

813
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,440
I don't have the address
of Xiaoyue's employers.

814
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,980
I think I heard Xiaoyue say

815
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,240
that her employers are at

816
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:35,720
some Jianghan Road in Wuhan,

817
00:32:35,770 --> 00:32:37,240
and they have a big silk shop.

818
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,030
What road?

819
00:32:38,310 --> 00:32:39,480
Jianghan Road.

820
00:32:40,030 --> 00:32:42,440
Is the young lady named Yu Shuzhen?

821
00:32:43,070 --> 00:32:43,920
How do you know?

822
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:44,920
The young lady is named

823
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,550
Yu Shuzhen or something.

824
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:49,040
Does Yu Shuzhen have a
fiancé surnamed Luo?

825
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,200
Young Master Luo!

826
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,750
He looks about as energetic as me,

827
00:32:51,750 --> 00:32:53,350
a bit paler and taller than me,

828
00:32:53,350 --> 00:32:55,510
and always has a pen clipped to his chest.

829
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:57,870
Father, he's talking about Zuliang.

830
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:58,970
Zuliang?

831
00:32:59,000 --> 00:32:59,920
Yes.

832
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:03,950
Zuliang looks nothing like him.

833
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:08,160
Zuliang is Aunt Yunkui's child.

834
00:33:08,180 --> 00:33:09,750
I remember when he was in university,

835
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:10,950
he studied medicine.

836
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,350
Yes, he studied medicine.

837
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:13,160
He's a doctor.

838
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:15,940
How is this world so small?

839
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:17,640
Originally, we went to Wuhan

840
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:19,040
to seek refuge with the Luo family.

841
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:20,440
I have already written a letter to them,

842
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:22,550
telling them we have arrived in Shanghai.

843
00:33:22,550 --> 00:33:24,240
The Luo family and the Yu family
are old friends.

844
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,570
Their houses are right next to each other.

845
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,350
So that means,

846
00:33:29,510 --> 00:33:30,960
I'm going to find Xiaoyue soon.

847
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,760
You should write a letter first.

848
00:33:36,350 --> 00:33:37,110
But...

849
00:33:37,110 --> 00:33:39,750
But I'm not very literate,

850
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,830
so my letters

851
00:33:42,790 --> 00:33:44,440
are always short.

852
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:55,480
But Master's handwriting

853
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:57,480
is widely recognized as beautiful.

854
00:34:20,010 --> 00:34:21,409
Why are you looking at me?

855
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:25,360
Aren't I the one who bites
the hand that feeds me,

856
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,670
and don't recognize your good intentions?

857
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:30,739
Master, I'll be the one
who bit the hand, okay?

858
00:34:31,070 --> 00:34:33,960
Please forgive my mistakes.

859
00:34:34,030 --> 00:34:37,070
Please bless me
with some of your calligraphy.

860
00:34:39,219 --> 00:34:40,020
Grind the ink.

861
00:34:41,230 --> 00:34:42,020
Okay.

862
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:45,440
Well.

863
00:34:53,190 --> 00:34:54,070
Master,

864
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,080
I don't have much education.

865
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:59,050
If I don't say things right,

866
00:34:59,190 --> 00:35:00,320
please bear with me.

867
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:02,110
Please don't laugh at me.

868
00:35:02,510 --> 00:35:04,440
It's just a letter home.

869
00:35:05,190 --> 00:35:07,290
It's not a memorial to the throne.

870
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:10,280
I will write down exactly what you say.

871
00:35:10,590 --> 00:35:11,440
Is that okay?

872
00:35:11,670 --> 00:35:13,590
It's not your fault
that you can't read much.

873
00:35:13,590 --> 00:35:15,550
Besides, having someone
write a letter for you

874
00:35:15,550 --> 00:35:16,840
is quite common.

875
00:35:17,070 --> 00:35:18,870
Just say whatever comes to mind.

876
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,160
Speak from your mind.

877
00:35:21,190 --> 00:35:23,230
Then I'll speak my mind.

878
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,590
Wife, I'm Wanfu.

879
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:36,400
What is your wife's name?

880
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,190
What?

881
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:39,760
It's Xiaoyue, Dad.

882
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,510
"Yue" as in the (yueliang)moon.

883
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:43,180
Yes, Xiaoyue.

884
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,480
My wife.

885
00:35:48,770 --> 00:35:50,920
[[Xiaoyue, when you read this,
it's as if I am right beside you.]

886
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,190
Master,

887
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:56,110
Wife, I'm Wanfu.

888
00:35:56,110 --> 00:35:57,120
That's 5 words.

889
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,070
Why did you write so many words?

890
00:35:59,070 --> 00:36:00,000
I recognize "Xiaoyue";

891
00:35:59,270 --> 00:36:01,140
[Xiaoyue, when you read this, it's
as if I am right beside you.]

892
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,440
What are the other words?

893
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:03,760
When you read this,
it's as if I am right beside you.

894
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:04,480
What?

895
00:36:04,590 --> 00:36:06,280
Xiaoyue, when you read this, it's
as if I am right beside you

896
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:07,480
Wait, who is "ruwu"?

897
00:36:07,510 --> 00:36:08,810
Why is she kissing him?

898
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,480
No.

899
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:15,710
This is the proper format for a letter.

900
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:17,290
It's not a person's name.

901
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:18,000
It means,

902
00:36:18,030 --> 00:36:19,670
Xiaoyue, seeing this letter
is like seeing me.

903
00:36:19,670 --> 00:36:20,710
That's right.

904
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:24,800
I see.

905
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:27,920
Then I'll continue.

906
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:35,880
"Xiaoyue, I'm now in Shanghai,

907
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:36,880
living in a western-style villa

908
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:38,840
inside the concession.

909
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:41,400
There are Master,

910
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,360
Madam,

911
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,730
Zhang Yunqi and those two troublemakers,

912
00:36:46,110 --> 00:36:47,070
and Yueming,

913
00:36:47,150 --> 00:36:48,480
just a child.

914
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:50,190
I'm listing all these names,

915
00:36:50,190 --> 00:36:51,320
but you probably won't even remember them.

916
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:52,150
Anyway,

917
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:53,320
I just wish you

918
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:55,230
were here.

919
00:36:55,930 --> 00:36:57,510
I miss you so much.

920
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,620
At night I can't sleep lying down,

921
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:01,880
I can't sleep sitting up,

922
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,550
I keep turning over and still can't sleep.

923
00:37:03,550 --> 00:37:04,880
I just miss you.

924
00:37:05,230 --> 00:37:06,760
I miss you

925
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,480
so much."

926
00:37:15,070 --> 00:37:15,840
Master,

927
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:17,510
I just said a whole bunch of things,

928
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:18,550
why did you

929
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,170
[Xiaoyue, when you read this, it's
as if I am right beside you.
I can't stop thinking about you
day and night.]

930
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,110
only write eight words?

931
00:37:20,110 --> 00:37:21,710
Are you buying cabbage

932
00:37:22,150 --> 00:37:23,800
and haggling over the weight?

933
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:25,920
I've already given you eight words.

934
00:37:26,110 --> 00:37:27,920
No, what did you write?

935
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:32,200
I can't stop thinking about you
day and night.

936
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,970
What does that mean?

937
00:37:34,110 --> 00:37:35,800
It means what you just said,

938
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:38,190
missing her so much.

939
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,150
That's what it means.

940
00:37:42,890 --> 00:37:43,660
Fine.

941
00:37:44,510 --> 00:37:45,320
Then...

942
00:37:47,510 --> 00:37:49,880
"Xiaoyue, the world is in chaos right now.

943
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:52,510
You must be careful in Wuhan.

944
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,740
Don't talk to strange men.

945
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:55,760
By the way,

946
00:37:56,190 --> 00:37:57,720
especially don't ever wear

947
00:37:58,030 --> 00:37:59,330
that gold hairpin.

948
00:37:59,590 --> 00:38:00,710
It's so bright;

949
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:02,590
if it catches a bad guy's eye

950
00:38:02,590 --> 00:38:04,510
and he has evil intentions,
what would you do?

951
00:38:04,510 --> 00:38:06,110
You'd better sew that gold hairpin

952
00:38:06,110 --> 00:38:07,110
into your clothes.

953
00:38:07,110 --> 00:38:07,910
Don't wear it.

954
00:38:08,030 --> 00:38:09,190
When I get to Wuhan,

955
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:11,220
you can wear it for me."

956
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:16,000
A seven-foot-tall man,

957
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:18,590
yet so petty and narrow-minded.

958
00:38:19,710 --> 00:38:20,840
I understand that—

959
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:24,540
"petty and narrow-minded"—
you're talking about me, aren't you?

960
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:29,450
I'm done writing. Yujiao will do it.

961
00:38:28,030 --> 00:38:29,370
[Xiaoyue, when you read this, it's
as if I am right beside you.
I can't stop thinking about you
day and night.]

962
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:31,960
Okay, okay, okay.

963
00:38:32,040 --> 00:38:33,300
I'll write it. I'll write it.

964
00:38:33,300 --> 00:38:34,230
Father.

965
00:38:37,510 --> 00:38:39,630
Only Yue Ming is sensible.

966
00:38:46,510 --> 00:38:48,150
See if this is okay.

967
00:38:48,710 --> 00:38:51,480
Xiaoyue, keep the gold hairpin I gave you

968
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:53,320
safe.

969
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:55,280
Don't show it off.

970
00:38:55,590 --> 00:38:57,280
And don't easily show it to others.

971
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:58,480
Is that what you mean?

972
00:38:59,230 --> 00:39:00,230
That's right.

973
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,550
That's not it at all.

974
00:39:08,630 --> 00:39:09,880
Then write,

975
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,190
"Xiaoyue,

976
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:15,510
whatever you eat, use, or spend in Wuhan—

977
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:17,380
[Keep the golden hairpin safe.
Don't be easy...]

978
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:17,230
just follow your young lady.

979
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,960
Eat and drink well with her,

980
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,030
and you won't suffer.

981
00:39:20,030 --> 00:39:21,420
You might even save quite a bit of money.

982
00:39:21,420 --> 00:39:22,350
But

983
00:39:22,550 --> 00:39:24,070
don't go running around everywhere

984
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,230
with her,

985
00:39:25,260 --> 00:39:28,440
especially things like handing out
leaflets or joining demonstrations.

986
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:30,800
That's what rich young ladies
and gentlemen do

987
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,430
when they've got nothing better to do.

988
00:39:32,430 --> 00:39:33,960
We're just ordinary folks—

989
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,180
let's not get involved in
national affairs.

990
00:39:35,180 --> 00:39:37,020
Staying alive and having food to eat
is the most important."

991
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:38,550
What are you talking about?

992
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:42,360
Miss Xiaoyue is loyal and patriotic.

993
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:43,760
Instead of helping her,

994
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:45,000
you're stopping her?

995
00:39:45,020 --> 00:39:47,880
I'm having a heart-to-heart talk
with our Xiaoyue.

996
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:48,840
Are you the one

997
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,000
having a heart-to-heart talk
with our Xiaoyue,

998
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:51,280
or am I?

999
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,360
Wanfu,

1000
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:58,250
even though you come from
humble beginnings,

1001
00:39:58,250 --> 00:40:01,280
you do have a sense of chivalry.

1002
00:40:01,790 --> 00:40:03,790
You saw it all along the way.

1003
00:40:03,890 --> 00:40:05,550
The nation is in peril.

1004
00:40:05,630 --> 00:40:07,800
It's the common people who suffer.

1005
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:11,280
When the nest is overturned,
no egg remains intact.

1006
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:14,760
With the skin gone,
what can the hair attach to?

1007
00:40:15,030 --> 00:40:17,510
What skin and hair?

1008
00:40:17,710 --> 00:40:19,190
What is skin and what is hair?

1009
00:40:19,190 --> 00:40:20,110
It means

1010
00:40:20,370 --> 00:40:21,860
the country is the skin,

1011
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:23,880
and the people are the hair.

1012
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,960
If the skin is gone,
how can the hair grow?

1013
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:26,920
If you're going to put it like that,

1014
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:28,980
then I really need to
argue with you today.

1015
00:40:28,980 --> 00:40:30,360
Since I arrived in Nanjing,

1016
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:31,230
entered your Zhang family,

1017
00:40:31,230 --> 00:40:32,710
and came all the way to Shanghai,

1018
00:40:32,710 --> 00:40:34,550
you keep throwing these words at me.

1019
00:40:34,550 --> 00:40:36,400
Are you taking advantage of the fact
that I don't understand?

1020
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:37,440
Let me tell you,

1021
00:40:37,710 --> 00:40:39,360
the skin you're talking about

1022
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:41,260
has never cared about this hair of mine.

1023
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:43,550
My parents died when I was little.

1024
00:40:43,630 --> 00:40:45,510
I begged all the way to Shanghai.

1025
00:40:45,550 --> 00:40:47,550
I was an apprentice for five years.

1026
00:40:47,590 --> 00:40:49,880
I finally managed to get enough to eat.

1027
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:50,460
Well,

1028
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:51,480
it's fine when there's no war.

1029
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:52,320
The skin and the hair

1030
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:53,400
mind their own business.

1031
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,840
But when a war breaks out,

1032
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:56,730
you can't expect us "hairs"

1033
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:59,130
to risk our lives for the "skin," can you?

1034
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:00,320
That makes no sense.

1035
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,400
It's not fair.

1036
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:03,290
I don't have any great abilities anyway.

1037
00:41:03,290 --> 00:41:04,630
I'm not going to attach myself
to that "skin"—

1038
00:41:04,630 --> 00:41:06,050
I'll just drift on my own.

1039
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:07,320
Nonsense!

1040
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,760
You are beyond saving!

1041
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:14,610
Beyond saving!

1042
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:16,230
I understand that one too.

1043
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:16,630
Fine.

1044
00:41:16,670 --> 00:41:18,320
-I am beyond saving.
-Enough! You two stop arguing.

1045
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,320
-Stop arguing.
-You're not worth working with.

1046
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:21,360
Fine, then don't work with me!

1047
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:22,630
I don't even want to work with you!

1048
00:41:22,630 --> 00:41:23,400
Dad,

1049
00:41:23,630 --> 00:41:25,070
I understand what Wanfu means.

1050
00:41:25,070 --> 00:41:26,000
Look, let's write it like this,

1051
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,000
"Xiaoyue,

1052
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:29,370
you and Miss Yu love and help each other,

1053
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:30,440
looking out for one another.

1054
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,800
I feel at ease in Shanghai."

1055
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:33,000
Is that what you mean?

1056
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:34,000
That's it.

1057
00:41:34,030 --> 00:41:35,060
No, it's not.

1058
00:41:35,110 --> 00:41:36,220
Yes, it is.

1059
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:37,620
Stop arguing!

1060
00:41:37,650 --> 00:41:38,850
Stop arguing!

1061
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:40,590
Dad,

1062
00:41:41,660 --> 00:41:43,320
take Yueming out for some sun.

1063
00:41:46,210 --> 00:41:47,940
You're not worth working with.

1064
00:41:52,390 --> 00:41:53,470
Keep writing.

1065
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:00,880
Madam,

1066
00:42:00,900 --> 00:42:02,900
the Master made me so mad I got confused.

1067
00:42:02,900 --> 00:42:04,900
Where were we?

1068
00:42:06,300 --> 00:42:07,220
You...

1069
00:42:10,860 --> 00:42:12,320
If you look out for each other,

1070
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:13,820
I'll feel at ease even here in Shanghai.

1071
00:42:13,820 --> 00:42:15,000
I am not at ease.

1072
00:42:15,030 --> 00:42:16,760
Are you going to write it or not?

1073
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:19,550
I'll write, I'll write.

1074
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,400
"Xiaoyue,

1075
00:42:25,430 --> 00:42:26,920
as soon as I save enough money,

1076
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:28,630
I will come to Wuhan
to find you right away.

1077
00:42:28,630 --> 00:42:30,830
You must wait for me in Wuhan.

1078
00:42:31,250 --> 00:42:32,210
Be good."

1079
00:42:42,520 --> 00:42:43,520
Okay.

1080
00:42:47,730 --> 00:42:49,280
Madam, you're making fun of me too.

1081
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,670
I'm not.

1082
00:42:53,370 --> 00:42:55,010
The sun is quite nice today.
